				Hey hey, what's with the anger.  I'm not debating in this thread.  I'm giving information.
<br />

<br />
1. Someone mentioned that Atta met with Iraqi intelligence.  This was wrong so I offered information correcting it.
<br />
2. Tried to get back onto the original post by offering a different view, which I never claimed to agree with.  I haven't even explored the link's ideas much. I thought it might be interesting as an avenue of exploration.
<br />
3. Someone said that the search for WMD was not a reason for the war.  So, I offered letters from Bush to congress and objectives from General Franks pointing out that the WMD issue cannot be denied as a very important issue in the decision to go to war.<br />
