You are arguing one little reason out of many and doing so by comparing apples and oranges.
<br />

<br />
Apples and oranges are both fruit.
<br />

<br />
I may hunger for an apple. Eating an orange will not neccessarily stop that hunger.
<br />

<br />
I may have a pork sandwich and prefer an apple with it.
<br />

<br />
When I look at the apple and the orange, I may find that the apple is more ripe.
<br />

<br />
Sadam Hussein was not the worlds only fruit.  He was the one that got eaten first.  But removing him does not require us to remove everyone else we dont like or have an issue with.  
<br />

<br />
Your arguement would mean that I would ahve to eat an orange EVERY time I ate an apple.  Then, of course, someone else is going to force bananas on me and pineapples as well.  The grape growers association will send me legal notice I suppose...
<br />

<br />
The idea is absurd.  Your arguement fails.
<br />

